headline: Is Global Payments (GPN) Undervalued After Its Recent 14% Share Price Rebound?
summary: Recent performance and why the stock is on radar Global Payments (GPN) has quietly bounced about 14% over the past month after a tough stretch this year, inviting a closer look at whether the payment tech provider is finally resetting expectations. See our latest analysis for Global Payments. That 14% 1 month share price return looks more like a sharp rebound than a full trend change. The share price is still down materially year to date and the 1 year total shareholder return remains...
